==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weft
<hw>Weft</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Waif</er>.]</ety> <def>A
thing waved, waived, or cast away; a waif.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧A forlorn <xex>weft</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weft</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Weft
<hw>Weft</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>weft</ets>,
<ets>wefta</ets>, fr. <ets>wefan</ets>, to weave. See
<er>Weave</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The woof of cloth; the threads that cross the warp
from selvage to selvage; the thread carried by the shuttle in
weaving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A web; a thing woven.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weftage</ent>⟦br⟧
